==English==

===Etymological Note===

The term ''news'' in the usual sense is simply derived from [[new]].  It is not an acronym for "North, East, West, South" or anything else.

===Noun===
# New information of interest.
#: ''Is there any news about the storm?''
#: ''That's news to me.''
# Reports of current events.
#: ''Did you listen to the news tonight?''

